races.description:
The Aeldari race has a long and complex spacefaring history, so long in fact that little is known for certain about the course of their physical evolution and early planet-bound existence. The original Aeldari homeworld was destroyed during the catastrophic collapse of the Aeldari civilisation known as the Fall of the Aeldari. The remnants of Aeldari culture that survived the cataclysm preserved much of their species' history in the form of traditional stories, songs and dance. Written records, monuments and visual records were almost completely destroyed except for a few instances where they were taken aboard voidcraft fleeing from the doomed worlds.

As a humanoid race, Aeldari are physically similar to humans, although not entirely identical by any means. They possess longer and cleaner limbs, and fine ascetic features with penetrating and slightly slanted, almond-shaped eyes. Their ears are also slightly pointed, but otherwise they could pass as human at first glance. The most obvious difference between humans and Aeldari can only be seen when they move, for the movements of an Aeldari radiate a subtle grace which is impossible for a human to emulate. This can be seen in even their slightest gestures or the dexterity with which they manipulate small objects.

The Aeldari mind, while similar in general to the human psyche, is far more inclined towards extremes. Because of this, Aeldari are more intelligent but also far more intense than humans. Although an Aeldari and a human can both feel grief or joy, the Aeldari's experience is likely to be far more extreme.
races.name: Dark Eldar

They retain vestigial beaks and have a light, almost hollow bone structure, with four digits on each hand and foot. Their skin is rough with small, barbed spines, similar to the elongated quills on their heads, protruding from various locations on their flesh. Skin pigmentation ranges from earthy brown colours and dappled greens to vibrant oranges and everything in between. Depending on the feeding directions of the Kroot Shapers, the colouration of each kindred can vary quite considerably. It is also common for Kroot from each kindred to have particular tribal markings painted onto their skin. Kroot mature quickly, with their most rapid period of growth occurring in the first ten years of their lives. By the age of twelve they are considered adults and it is not unknown for Kroot to live to over a hundred years old, their skin becoming increasingly pitted and leathery in their last few years of life
races.name: Kroot

races.description:
The Tau are generally shorter than humans, smaller in stature and with less muscle mass and body weight. Every Tau is humanoid in shape, with two arms,[17] two cloven feet, and a single head. Their grey-blue skin is leathery and tough and exudes no moisture, owing to the generally dry conditions of their homeworld. Their faces are flat, wide around the eyes, and their olfactory organs are located inside their mouths. Their eyes can see into the infrared and ultraviolet. Tau eyesight is good, but they focus on distant objects slower than humans. The Tau are not very good in close combat, as they find the whole concept uncivilized.

The Tau has three digits and a single opposable thumb on each hand. The main difference from humans is the bone structure of Tau's lower legs, feet and ankles. Tau have shorter bones of the libia and fibia, but their feet have elongated cuneiform bones and talus and two large central weight-bearing toes. The Tau have eveolved to stand and move without using their heels.[17]
races.name: Tau

races.description: The Vespid are a unique race of insect-like aliens who are members of the T'au Empire. In the T'au Lexicon, they are called "Mal'kor." This derives from the T'au words for insect, "Mal," and air, "Kor." The soldiers of the Imperium of Man often refer to them as "Stingwings." The Vespids' homeworld is a gas giant also called Vespid, three light years to the galactic south of the T'au's D'yanoi Sept.
races.name: Vespid

races.description: The pinnacle of the orkoid species: A fully grown Ork.
races.name: Ork

races.description:
Gretchin or Grotz are basically a smaller subspecies of Orks, who are more cowardly than normal Orks and are usually used as living shields, to clear mine fields, are stepped on to get through difficult terrain, and sometimes even as emergency rations. Gretchins are quite low in the strict hierarchy of Ork society because of their small size (the lowest Orkoids being the Snotlings) and are often used for the dirtiest jobs like scavenging and being used as the football when the bigger Orks get bored.

While they are not as aggressive as standard Orks, they enjoy fighting weaker opponents and are less likely to flee if they comfortably outnumber their opponents. If a Gretchin is particularly wealthy, he may purchase a second-hand, worn-down, low-tech gun. These guns are mainly to reassure the Gretchin that they have a chance of killing something, provided they remember which way to hold the gun.
races.name: Grot

races.description: The most distinguishing feature of turians is their metallic carapace. The turians evolved this trait as a defense against the greater levels of solar radiation that penetrate their homeworld's weak magnetic field.
races.name: Turian

races.description: The krogan are a species of large reptilian bipeds native to the planet Tuchanka, a world known for its harsh environments, scarce resources, and overabundance of vicious predators.
races.name: Krogan

races.description: The geth are a race of networked artificial intelligences that reside beyond the Perseus Veil. The geth were created by the quarians as laborers and tools of war. When the geth became sentient and began to question their masters, the quarians attempted to exterminate them.
races.name: Geth

races.description: The geth are a race of networked artificial intelligences that reside beyond the Perseus Veil. The geth were created by the quarians as laborers and tools of war. When the geth became sentient and began to question their masters, the quarians attempted to exterminate them.
races.name: Geth Prime

races.description: A form of mechanized infantry, produced during an ancient time on this rimworld. These units are very strong, powerful war machines but are subsequently slow and have limited battery to them.
races.name: M7 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A prototype M7 mechanized infantry, equipped with a limited SkyCore unit and SkyMind radio. These units are very strong, powerful war machines and allow digital consciousness to move on battlefields but are subsequently slow and have limited internal storage capacity to them.
races.name: M8 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A lost android, shunned from their transcendant community. The tech used to make them is beyond human comprehension, boasting near unlimited power and requiring little sustinence to operate. They deem all races other than themselves to be somewhat below them and believe that living on a rimworld is a fate worse than death.
races.name: T5 Android

races.description: The most advanced form of android conceivable; this tier is able to efficiently hold the consciousness of any AI uploaded onto it, with advanced locomotive abilities and manipulation; this android vastly suprasses most humans.
races.name: T4 Android

races.description: A Prototype android exclusive to this rimworld; developed by a secret R/D Laboratory, away from the eye of the rest of the planet and cosmos. This android features highly advanced locomotive and motor abilities, perfectly mimicing that of an average human. Although clunky and somewhat slow - this android features a modular component design, allowing for upgrades to be made to current parts at any point.
races.name: T3 Android

races.description: As simple as sentient robotics can get. This design is the bare skeletal amount of components needed to create full autonomous functionality. Obviously not the best but it works well when needed.
races.name: T1 Android

races.description: A somewhat advanced android, capable of almost perfectly storing an AI consciousness and with reasonable levels of motor skills. A good all round android that is uses extensively on glitterworlds for basic maintenance and cleaning.
races.name: T2 Android

races.description: A demon hailing from the realm of Slaanesh. They are quick and agile fighters that dances around the battlefiel with grace and speed. They make excellent fighters but they tend to have cruel streaks and lack in the handy department.
races.name: daemonette

races.description: A human lured to the dark embrace of Slaanesh. They tend to be a bit colder personality wise but they are still human, mostly. Mutations can vary.
races.name: slaaneshi human

races.description: As perverse as any other follower of Slaanesh, these Daemon Princes are twisted into a form more pleasing to their master. These Daemon Princes are lither and far more graceful in their actions than Daemon Princes that serve the other ruinous powers. Their current form my restrict their ability to wear some apparel.
races.name: slaanesh prince

races.description: A very large and imposing reptile-like humanoid with massive, razor sharp claws that can rip armored and unarmored foes to ribbons with ease. They possess incredible strength and durable hides taht grant them resillience to most forms of damage and the elements alike. However, their mental and social abilities are often below that of the average human and their claws make tasks requiring careful manipulation slow and difficult.
races.name: Deathcloid

races.description: Whether due to scientific experimentation, occult interference, or comic fluke, these are poor souls for whom death has been abjured.
races.name: reanimated corpse

races.description: A curious Fennex race, known for their obsession with information and love for dry climates.
races.name: Fennex

races.description: A curious Fox race, known for their obsession with information and resistance to cold.
races.name: Frijjid

races.description: Elegant mono-gender race. Native to the planet Thessia, Asari are often considered the most influential and respected sentient species in the galaxy, and are known for their, diplomacy and biotic aptitude. Asari can often use biotic powers without the need of biotic amplifiers.
races.name: asari

races.description:
The Renamon race is a Digital-Animal Hybrid vessel by injecting data indexes to form the appearance of a fox.
Its slender, tall appearance excels in combat when faced with enemies of similar size, with various fighting arts that use its speed and agility for quick attacks.
Being a stoic combination of Holo-Matrix and Nanites, Renamon are usually calm, cool, and collected, and don't lose their composure in most situations.
races.name: Renamon

races.description: A curious raccoon race, known for their obsession with information.
races.name: Racc

races.description: A mutant of the catgirl species that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Catgirl

races.description: A mutant of the wolfgirl species that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Wolfgirl

races.description: A mutant of the foxgirl species that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Foxgirl

races.description: A Cowgirl that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Cowgirl

races.description: A Harpy that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Harpy

races.description: A mutant accumulation of slimy liquid that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Slime

races.description: A Baphomet that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Baphomet

races.description: A Centaur that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Centaur

races.description: A mutant of the Forest Fairy species that has developed a semblance of intelligence./n A fragile existence that withers in a toxic environment.
races.name: ForestFairy

races.description: A mutant of the Ice Fairy species that has developed a semblance of intelligence./n A fragile existence that cannot survive warm temperatures.
races.name: IceFairy

races.description: A mutant of the Dragon species that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Dragon

races.description: A mutant of the Thrumbogirl species that has developed a semblance of intelligence.
races.name: Thrumbogirl

races.description: It is a race where foxes took on the mystical powers of the transcendent world and took on human form. Their body has an elegans organ in which the strength of their superpowers is determined by the amount of sunlight interlocked with the mechanite in their body. Thanks to this organ, foxes revere the sun and energy.
races.name: Miho

races.description: Lombax is a distant descendant of human race with feline features. Representatives of this species are great warriors and engineers. Despite their size, their bodies are surprisingly tough. Lombaxes are originated from Fastoon - glitterworld with dry desert climate. They prefer to live in hot enviroment.
races.name: Lombax

races.description: Kijins are ogres who were evolved alikes of humans. Their huge bodies and muscles have shrunk, but the muscles are more dense and stronger. They still have to eat a lot to keep themselves up.
races.name: Kijin

races.description: The Assaultron unit is a nimble assassin robot.
races.name: Assaultron

races.description: The Mister Gutsy, unlike the Mister Handy, is a dedicated combat robot. This model was commissioned by the U.S. Army just before the Great War.
races.name: Mister Gutsy

races.description: The first Mister Handy was introduced to the robotics market in 2037 by General Atomics International, as a general purpose construction and maintenance unit. Used widely on both the American and Mexican markets (especially after the Mexico City earthquake of 2042), it was a rugged, reliable design. So reliable, in fact, that it only received one major hardware update in 2039, to eliminate a bug causing interference in the operation of the multiple arms. The Calpower 238B nuclear power unit and self-maintenance modes were key to its success, ensuring each robot's longevity. To minimize maintenance overhead, each Mr. Handy was designed to perform its own nuclear fuel replacement and radiation cleansing, as well as carry out maintenance and repairs on other units (it was not possible for it to carry it out on itself).
races.name: Mister Handy

races.description: A version of Mr. Handy encountered at Milton General Hospital, with two saw blade attachments.
races.name: Nurse Handy

races.description: The Protectetron unit is a slow worker.
races.name: Protectetron

races.description: The Scrapbot unit is a small weak melee fighted made to haul.
races.name: Scrapbot

races.description: The Securitron unit is a mass-produced robot meant to keep a meaningful prescence and keep the peace.
races.name: Securitron

races.description: The Sentrybot unit is a thicc tanky robot.
races.name: Sentrybot

races.description: A curious Ferret race, known for their business acumen.
races.name: Ferrex

races.description: A non feral ghoul, is a decrepit, rotting, zombie-like mutant. Intense and prolonged radiation has ravaged their skin, much of their flesh and in some cases many of their ligaments.
races.name: ghoul

races.description: A non feral glowing ghoul, is a decrepit, rotting, zombie-like mutant. Intense and prolonged radiation has ravaged their skin, much of their flesh and in some cases many of their ligaments. It emits a powerful glow capable of growing plants.
races.name: glowing one

races.description: A hardy human-cactus hybrid species able to live in harse conditions.
races.name: cactoid

races.description: A strange and mysterious reptilian race, known for their connection to an even more mysterious tree called the Hist.
races.name: Argonian

races.description:
A race of humanlike robots which are mostly female in model variety.

The origins of these machines are mostly unknown. Some speculate they are escapees from a civilization which used them for labor and some just suggest they are outdated pleasure machines which got dumped by a passing space freighter.

By design by their previous masters they are weak physically but their raw fortitude is enough to make up for it. Beware of their biological reactor and capacitors violently exploding, if they die by overheating.
races.name: Android

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike worker robots.

Usually found toiling around in colonies around the rim which got a resident tinkerer.

Not capable of sapience, however their relative cheap cost and ability to work around the clock make them valuable workers.
races.name: Droid

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike warrior robots.

Usually found guarding the homes of the wealthy and offices of mega corporations. They show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves. Are traditionally armed with miniguns and core launchers.
races.name: Battledroid

races.description:
A race of spacer-tech humanlike worker robots.

Usually found toiling around in colonies around the rim which got a resident tinkerer.Not capable of sapience making them perfect for colony tasks. 

Advanced droids are much better than their outdated models in every way. 

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: Advanced droid

races.description:
A race of spacer-tech humanlike warrior robots.

Installed into military bases and highly sensitive areas. They show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves. Are traditionally armed with miniguns and core launchers.

Advanced droids are much better than their outdated models in every way. Wardroids possess four arms, each of which is highly deadly. Humans beware: bring an army to defeat this model.

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: Wardroid

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This device is masterful in building & mining, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: engineer

races.description:
Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This device is masterful in tasks relating to food & farming. It's designed to ensure everyone is fed and the kitchen is stocked.

This drone is unable to do combat nor any other skilled jobs.
races.name: chef

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This drone is highly capable in medicine, and is able to take care of most typical injuries.
races.name: medic

races.description: A human, modified by gene engineering and designed evolutionary pressures.
races.name: Astarte Space Marine (HAR)

races.description: The resulting type of Android when Crystalloids were used as a template. This exceedingly rare variant of androids are not quite like a Crystalloid nor a standard Android.
races.name: crystalloid android
